{"id": "gram2-pos-items", "rules": ["GRAM-2"], "expect": {"kind": "run", "exit": 0}, "status": "runnable", "reason": "No protected negative is assigned to this positive case. Under v0.9, malformed item grammar is attributed deterministically by DIAG-1 and the source EBNF; additive diagnostic cases are separate.", "doc": "GRAM-2: a program is item* \u2014 here two fn_decl items and one enum_decl item; compiles and runs to exit 0."}
{"id": "gram3-pos-modes", "rules": ["GRAM-3"], "expect": {"kind": "accept"}, "status": "runnable", "reason": "No protected negative is assigned to this positive case. Under v0.9, malformed type or mode syntax receives deterministic source-EBNF attribution through DIAG-1.", "doc": "GRAM-3: the three modes own / &'r / &uniq 'r written explicitly on i32 params, with a region_param declaring 'r; accepted."}
